  {
    "id": 8978371685,
    "title": "Client is asking for a different booking widget to be integrated",
    "list_title": "QUESTIONS/DISCUSSIONS:",
    "completed": true,
    "due_on": null,
    "created_at": "2025-08-19T14:36:06.891Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-10-03T21:45:21.874Z",
    "completed_on": "2025-10-03T21:45:05.338Z",
    "comments_count": 15,
    "assignees": "Chris Traynor, Justyna Acosta",
    "app_url": "https://3.basecamp.com/4226914/buckets/42475931/todos/8978371685",
    "description": "<div>Jeff arranged a call on Friday with me and one of his partners from that private equity group.<br><br>The partner had two objectives. He wanted to ask me questions to see if he could determine whether I knew what I was talking about and whether we had \"our head up our ass\". Apparently, my head was in the correct place on Friday.<br><br>He also asked if we could integrate a different booking widget, as the one they use now \"sucks\".<br><br>They are also looking to move away from Scheduler Pro (the native Service Titan scheduler), and ideally, they said they like the one being used on <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" class=\"autolinked\" data-behavior=\"truncate\" href=\"https://www.semperfiheatingcooling.com/\">https://www.semperfiheatingcooling.com/</a><br><br>Unfortunately, that is a wordpress site, and it seems what they are using is an integration with Gravity Forms. Given that their site is built on Wordflow, I told them I'd need help looking into what options exist.<br><br>Jeff texted me yesterday asking if we had a solution yet. I said I hadn't had enough time.<br><br>I need to know what options exist, and also, they are mildly curious what it would cost to convert the site back to wordpress. If there's a way to embed a different scheduling tool I need that sooner, as they don't want to wait for the new site before making the switch.</div>",
    "visible_to_clients": false
  },
